title: Album Page, "Elevation of Door with Symbols of François I, Chambord", ca. 1889
medium: Graphite on textured off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, top right corner: 80; bottom right corner: 68; to right of drawing: Chambord -.
description: Vertical sheet depicting a wooden door with only the upper half articulated.  The door has an inset round-arched panel divided by a vertical member.  The left side contains a capital F with small, scrolling serifs protruding from all three ends, while the right side contains a salamander facing to the right with its head looking backward over its shoulder. Above it is a small crown while the rest of the panel has small dancing flames, which also decorate the corners of the door.
